{
  "name": "Expert Spellblade",
  "type": "feature",
  "img": "icons/magic/unholy/hand-weapon-glow-black-green.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>You gain the following benefits for your Spellblade Class Features.</p><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Bound Weapon</span></strong></span></p><p><strong>Bound Damage:</strong> Your Bound Damage now ignores Resistance to its damage type.</p><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spellblade Discipline</span></strong></span></p><p>You gain 1 Additional Spellblade Discipline.</p><p>The following Disciplines are changed in the following ways:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Acolyte:</strong> You can spend additional MP to increase the healing by 2 for each additional MP spent.</p></li><li><p><strong>Hex Warrior:</strong> You can spend additional MP increase the damage by 1 for each additional MP spent.</p></li><li><p><strong>Spell Warder:</strong> When you gain the Resistance granted by Spell Warder, you can spend 1 MP to gain Resistance (Half) to the damage type instead.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spellstrike</span></strong></span></p><p>The Spell you cast as part of Spellstrike can target multiple creatures or an Area, provided at least one of the Spell targets is also a target of the Martial Attack.</p>",
